{
  "stem": "12674.2",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "As I was saying, I learned Hebrew, and I was speaking it pretty well by the time I was 12 years old.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And when I came to Israel, in the way from-- in the way from the airport to the-- to the hotel, I was sitting in the taxi, and I could read all the street signs and all the things.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But I couldn't read it freely because I had been disconnected from it.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So I couldn't help myself, and I brought out my finger.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And my finger was going like this in the taxi, and I became very embarrassed because I felt very stupid sitting there with that finger.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So I-- I sat on my hands.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I was sitting in the taxi, and I couldn't-- I wanted to read all the signs because it was interesting-- a butcher, a dress store, whatever, or with some, you know, some advertisements or something.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But I couldn't-- I couldn't really read without my finger, and which had no connection, because-- and-- and I was forever jumping up and down on the taxi seat.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So I was very unhappy because I-- when I was walked out in the street, I didn't understand what people were saying.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So one day we had-- we had-- my brother was at that time living in Israel.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He had moved there from New York.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I was babysitting his two children.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I was in the house, and my aunt was coming, the-- my father's younger sister, Adele, had managed to get out of Vienna before we were all sent-- we were all deported in 1938.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And she went on Israel on aliyah, and we don't know if they're illegals.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And she-- she was there since 1938.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
